      "text": "CVE-2024-7890: A critical remote code execution vulnerability (CWE-78) has been actively exploited in the wild against Apache Tomcat version 9.0.65. The flaw was discovered in the request parsing module where unsanitized user input is passed directly to the system() function call without proper validation.",
